The paper deals with image tag completion, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves low-rank factorization and sparse coding, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of local linear reconstruction structures, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for tag completion, which could be considered as a contribution to the field of artificial intelligence, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
